WHO   — Cron — the time-based job scheduler at the heart of Unix and its descendants — a daemon that runs commands at fixed times, dates, or intervals, forever, without supervision
WHAT  — the time-based job scheduler at the heart of Unix and its descendants — a daemon that runs commands at fixed times, dates, or intervals, forever, without supervision
WHERE — CRN · The Cron Job — Unix scheduling, ~1975 → today (LOGISMÓS domain)  Framework inputs: cron; crontab; crond; the schedule; the box; the watch  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — It is the machine's first autonomy: the oldest layer that acts on its own clock, the quiet engine under most of the world's scheduled work.
HOW   — Crystallized from the history & practice of cron.

